Looks like @JalenM32 's leg is doing just fine. He races behind the TFA defense for a 61-yard TD catch from Harrell. Wolves down 31-29.
Parker Mara records his second pick of the game for TFA
Camden Hicks converts a 38-yard field goal, increasing TFA's lead to 31-21 in the fourth quarter.
Three quarters in the books... First Academy leads Deltona, 28-21.
Rolous Frazier tops the 100-yard rushing mark for TFA tonight
Ramel Harrell has 126 yards on three carries, two for TDs.
Monroe walks off, which is good. Ramel Harrell runs 71 yards for a TD on the next play, which is better. Deltona back within 28-21.
Jalen Monroe stays down after a 9-yard reception across the middle.
First Academy opens the second half with a touchdown drive. Alex Shields rips away an 18-yard score from a Deltona defender. 28-14, Royals.
And it's finally halftime. TFA leads Deltona 21-14.
TFA leads Deltona 21-14 in the second
TOUCHDOWN, @DeltonaFootball . Ramel Harrell off to the races for a 45-yard TD. Caught TFA off guard with a shotgun keeper.
Ramel Harrell taking some snaps at QB now. Nick Christiano is 3 of 7 for 50 yards and an INT.
Deltona will get another crack late in the first half. No operating scoreboard, so no clue how much time's left.
Deltona gets it right back on the next play as TFA bobbles a handoff.
Nick Christiano goes deep on first down, overthrows Jalen Monroe in double coverage and gets picked off. Parker Mara with the INT for TFA.
TFA has rolled up 203 yards and 10 first down on its first four possessions
TOUCHDOWN, @TFA_Athletics . Pretty throw and catch from Alex Eleyssami to Parker Mara, good for a 23-yard score. Royals lead 21-7.
Wolves are 0 for 3 on third down, forced to punt it back to TFA as they trail 14-7 in the second.
TOUCHDOWN, @TFA_Athletics . Lake Ellis goes 5 yards untouched on a counter. TFA leads Deltona 14-7 in the second.
END OF THE FIRST QUARTER: Deltona 7, Orlando First Academy 7
Deltona fails to convert on 4th-and-3 from the TFA 47.
Deltona tightens up defensively on TFA's second possession, including a pair of negative runs. Royals go 3-and-out.
TOUCHDOWN, @DeltonaFootball . Tremon Bright (@Tremon2lhTremon) scores a 2-yard TD on fourth down. 7-7 in the first quarter.
Wow. What a catch by @JalenM32 . Took it away from a defender for a 36-yard gain. Looked like a pick for sure.
TFA goes 75 yards on 8 plays to take a 7-0 lead over Deltona
First-and-goal for TFA at the 2. And Rolous Frazier immediately punches it in after a 27-yard hookup from Alex Eleyssami to Alex Shields.
Royals gain 35 yards on their first three plays. Deltona's defense has eight new starters.
TFA will start with the ball. No opening kickoff. Here we go.
Welp. No Deltona roster in sight. This should be fun.

Sha'Kawanza Brown ties the game again. 46-46 in the dying seconds.
Sha'Kawanza Brown floater. 46-44 FPC. And Walker misses a layup off a steal. Goodness.
Green splits the pair. 46-42 FPC.
Walker adds a bucket for NSB to cut the deficit to 45-42. But Skye Green gets fouled off a pump fake in the post. She'll go to the line.

But @CWALK1__ gets it back with a 3 from the left corner. NSB 29-27, 6:23 4th.
Dyman Howard jumper, followed by a pair of Skye Green free throws. FPC leads 27-26.
Three quarters in the books, New Smyrna Beach leads Flagler Palm Coast 26-23.
Playing a decent game tonight. New system, but same group. Seven seniors. Likely won't be pushed much until regionals.
Princess Thomas gets the and-1 to extend New Smyrna's lead to 24-17 late in the third quarter.

Steal and transition bucket for @CWALK1__ , plus the and-1. New Smyrna Beach leads 16-12 with less than 3 minutes left in the second.
FPC leads 12-8 after one quarter. Jimaya Baker and Skye Green each have 4 points for the Bulldogs.
6-6 in a fast-paced start. @CWALK1__ with four early points for the Barracudas.

Na'Shawn Lewis called for unsportsmanlike conduct for standing up over the receiver after a TFL. Baker at the SF 32.
